Bheki Cele is still out in Durban today, monitoring level three lockdown compliance. Cele will also be judging whether the province's festive season safety plans are working. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister, Bheki Cele, is urging police not to be too heavy-handed over level three restrictions. But reiterates if they are under threat they can use force. He warns that criminals won't get any leniency for committing crimes. READ: Cele tells police officers to be decisive when dealing with crime "It is not in the Constitution to be brutal, you don't have to be brutal but again, it's not in the Constitution to let criminals go," he said. Police presence is expected to increase significantly as we head into the New Year. For more, watch the video above